image_data_augument = dict(
    # rescale            = None, #  rescaling factor. If None or 0, no rescaling is applied, otherwise multiply the data by the value provided
    samplewise_std_normalization = False, # divide each input by its std
    # points outside the boundaries ('constant', 'nearest', 'reflect' or 'wrap'). 
    # 'constant': kkkkkkkk|abcd|kkkkkkkk (cval=k) 
    # 'nearest': aaaaaaaa|abcd|dddddddd 
    # 'reflect': abcddcba|abcd|dcbaabcd 
    # 'wrap': abcdabcd|abcd|abcdabcd
    # fill_mode          = 'nearest',
    # cval = 0, #value used for fill_mode 'constant'

    rotation_range     = 30.0, # degrees (0 to 180)

    width_shift_range = 0.1, # fraction of total width, if < 1, or pixels if >= 1.
    height_shift_range= 0.1, # fraction of total height, if < 1, or pixels if >= 1.
    # shear_range       = 0.0, # shear intensity (shear angle in degrees).
    # zoom_range        = 0.5, # amount of zoom. if scalar z, zoom will be randomly picked in the range [1-z, 1+z]. A sequence of two can be passed instead to select this range.

    horizontal_flip   = True, # whether to randomly flip images horizontally

In [19]:
# CALLBACKS
callbacks = []

# + ModelCheckPoint
template_name= "%s_{epoch:02d}_{val_loss:.3f}_val_acc-{val_accuracy:.3f}.h5"%(params["model_name"])
print(f"+ Template name: {template_name}")
modekcheckpoint_callback = ModelCheckpoint(filepath = os.path.join(checkpoints_dir, template_name),
                                           monitor='val_accuracy', 
                                           verbose=1, 
                                           save_best_only=True, 
                                           save_weights_only=False, # only weight, 
                                           mode='auto', # min, max, auto
                                           period=1  # bao nhieu epoch moi xem xet 1 lan
                                          )
callbacks.append(modekcheckpoint_callback)

# + Early Stopping: Stop training when a monitored quantity has stopped improving.
if params["early_stopping"]>0:
    earlystopping_callback = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience= params["early_stopping"])
    callbacks.append(earlystopping_callback)
    print("+ Early Stopping: ", params["early_stopping"])
# if

# csv_logger_callback = CSVLogger(os.path.join(logs_dir, 'train.log'))
# callbacks.append(csv_logger_callback)

# + Visualize logs
review_logs = {}
review_columns = []
def custom_on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs, **kwargs):  
    review_logs = kwargs["review_logs"]
    review_columns = kwargs["review_columns"]
    lr = K.eval(self.model.optimizer.lr)
    if epoch == 0:
        review_logs["epoch"] = [epoch]
        review_columns.append("epoch")
        
        for key in logs.keys(): review_logs[key] = [logs[key]]
        review_columns.extend(logs.keys())
        
        review_logs["lr"] = [lr]
        review_columns.append("lr")
    else:
        review_logs["epoch"].append(epoch)
        review_logs["lr"].append(lr)
        for key in logs.keys(): review_logs[key].append(logs[key])
    # if
    
    df_logs = pd.DataFrame(review_logs, columns = review_columns)
    df_logs.to_csv(os.path.join(logs_dir, 'train.log'), index = False)
    
    visualize_data = review_logs
    group_view     = [{"x": "epoch", "y": ["loss", "val_loss"], 
                       "title": "Loss at Epoch {epoch}: {val_loss:.6f}\n", 
                       "style": "median"}, 
                      {"x": "epoch", "y": ["accuracy", "val_accuracy"], 
                       "title": "Accuracy at Epoch {epoch}: {val_accuracy:.6f}\n", 
                       "style": "median"},
                      {"x": "epoch", "y": ["lr"], 
                       "title": "Learning Rate\n", 
                       "style": None}
                     ]
    fig = visualize_logs(visualize_data, group_view, figsize = (20, 6), is_show = False, 
                         save_path = os.path.join(logs_dir, "logs.png"))
    plt.close()
    if epoch == 0:
        display.display(fig, display_id="logs")
    else:
        display.update_display(fig, display_id="logs")
    pass
# custom_on_epoch_end

if params["clr"] is not None:
    clr_callbacks = CyclicLR(**params["clr"])
    print("+ CLR: ", params["clr"])
    callbacks.append(clr_callbacks)
# if

custom_callbacks = LambdaCallback()
custom_callbacks.on_epoch_end = lambda epoch, logs: custom_on_epoch_end(custom_callbacks, epoch, logs, 
                                                                        review_logs = review_logs, review_columns = review_columns)
callbacks.append(custom_callbacks)

starting_time = time.time()
model.fit_generator(generator       = train_gen, 
                    
                    initial_epoch   = initial_epoch,
                    epochs          = final_epoch,
                    steps_per_epoch = steps_per_epoch,

                    validation_data = valid_gen,
                    validation_steps= validation_steps,

                    verbose         = 1
)
